cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a new approach for collaborative filtering using spectral regularization to learn linear operators. It also provides learning algorithms based on low-rank decompositions, which is a common technique in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as collaborative filtering is a common technique used in recommendation systems, which are often used in information retrieval applications. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as collaborative filtering is a popular technique in AI for building recommendation systems. 

It may also fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as collaborative filtering is often used in social networks for personalized recommendations. 

Finally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper discusses matrix completion approaches to collaborative filtering, which is a common problem in data structures and algorithms.
